From 3a5ce6920b80df166c151e038c6463d0c82244c0 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Z User <z@container>
Date: Tue, 23 Jun 2026 17:07:47 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix(critical): fix gamepad not detected + Shizuku service
 disappearing
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Three root cause bugs fixed end-to-end:

BUG 1 (CRITICAL): Gamepad not detected in GamepadTester
Root cause: GamepadPlugin (Android native KeyEvent/MotionEvent handler)
emitted events on 'gamepadEvent' channel, but NO frontend code listened
to that channel. Only Shizuku-based events ('onGamepadButton') were used.
Since Android WebView does NOT support navigator.getGamepads() Web API,
gamepad was invisible when Shizuku getevent was not running.

Fix: GamepadPlugin now emits on BOTH channels:
- 'gamepadEvent' (legacy, for backward compat)
- 'onGamepadButton'/'onGamepadAxis' (via TouchInjectionPlugin companion)
This means native Android gamepad input (which works WITHOUT Shizuku)
is now forwarded to the frontend.

BUG 2 (CRITICAL): Shizuku service disappears from management
Root cause: TouchInjectionPlugin.bindService() called
Shizuku.unbindUserService(USER_SERVICE_ARGS, serviceConnection, true)
with third parameter 'true' (removeUserService=true). This KILLS the
service process every time re-binding occurs (e.g., on app resume).
Every app background → resume cycle killed and re-created the service,
causing it to disappear from Shizuku management.

Fix: Changed third parameter to 'false' (removeUserService=false) in
bindService(). Only unbindService() (explicit user action) uses 'true'.

BUG 3 (CRITICAL): useGamepadLoop only set up listeners when Shizuku connected
Root cause: useGamepadLoop useEffect returned early if !connected,
skipping listener setup entirely. Even though GamepadPlugin now emits
on 'onGamepadButton', no listener was registered to receive it.

Fix: Split into setupListeners() (always runs) and setupShizuku() (only
when connected). Listeners are always active so native Android gamepad
events are received regardless of Shizuku status.

Combined effect: Gamepad now works in GamepadTester even WITHOUT Shizuku
(via Android native input). Shizuku service persists across app lifecycle.
Touch injection still requires Shizuku for getevent + MotionEvent injection.
